The paper discusses graph-based approaches for approximate nearest neighbor search, which is a problem commonly encountered in computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The analysis of the performance of these algorithms is based on their underlying data structures, which suggests that the paper could also be classified under computer science - data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
